  "doc_id": "11204",
  "text": "The resultant taxa abundance tables were used to calculate observed and expected species richness, alpha diversity indices, and beta diversity distance matrices. At each taxonomic level, microbial taxa which were present in all the subjects, irrespective of their relative abundances, were considered as core microbiome. Principle Coordinate Analysis (PCoA) was performed to cluster samples based on abundance Jaccard distance matrix (community structure). Differentially abundant taxa at the species and strain levels were identified using Linear discriminant analysis Effect Size (LEfSe) [CITATION_1] , with 'caries' and 'caries-free' as classes and 'early-caries' and 'advanced caries' as subclasses.",
